Phylogenetic signal for urban tolerance of Columbidae species

library(phytools)
library(dplyr)
library(tidyverse)

Load a maximum clade credibility tree from jetz

tree <- read.tree("./phylogeny__stage2_hackett_mcc_no_neg.tre")

Load urban tolerance data ## Read in data exported from bigquery

models:
  - name: all_columbidae_communities
    description: Regional and urban communities for all cities with a population of at least 250,000 from GHSL Data Package 2019 (Pesaresi et al. 2019), which contain at leasts 167 eBird checklists, and have at least one Columbidae species within their regional pools.
    columns:
      - name: city_id
        description: Vector ID from GHSL Data Package 2019 (Pesaresi et al. 2019)
      - name: city_name
        description: City name from Vector from GHSL Data Package 2019 (Pesaresi et al. 2019)
      - name: jetz_scientific_name
        description: The mapped name of each species whose distribution from BirdLife International’s species distribution maps (BirdLife International and Handbook of the Birds of the World 2020), overlaps with the city vector from GHSL Data Package 2019 (Pesaresi et al. 2019). Species mapped from eBird and Birdlife to JETZ taxonomy using birdlife alternative names and Avibase (Lepage 2011).
      - name: present_in_city
        description: True if the species is present on at least 5% of all valid checklists within the city
      - name: season_code 
        description: season code from BirdLife International and Handbook of the Birds of the World 2020
      - name: season
        description: Textual description of Birdlife's season code
      - name: origin_code 
        description: origin code from BirdLife International and Handbook of the Birds of the World 2020
      - name: origin
        description: Textual description of Birdlife's origin code
all_columbidae_presence = read_csv('bigquery_export__columbidae_jetz_urban_locations.csv')


── Column specification ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
cols(
  city_id = col_double(),
  city_name = col_character(),
  jetz_scientific_name = col_character(),
  present_in_city = col_logical(),
  season_code = col_double(),
  season = col_character(),
  origin_code = col_double(),
  origin = col_character()
)
head(all_columbidae_presence)

Create urban tolerance for each species based on the number of cities / number of regional pools

Check for species from data not in tree

columbidae_urban_tolerance[!columbidae_urban_tolerance$jetz_scientific_name %in% tree$tip.label,]

Number of species in analysis:

nrow(columbidae_urban_tolerance)
[1] 160

Format data

columbidae_input_species <- columbidae_urban_tolerance[columbidae_urban_tolerance$jetz_scientific_name %in% tree$tip.label,]
tree_pruned_to_columbidae <- ladderize(drop.tip(tree, setdiff(tree$tip.label, columbidae_urban_tolerance$jetz_scientific_name)))

columbidae_response <- columbidae_input_species$urban_tolerance
names(columbidae_response) <- columbidae_input_species$jetz_scientific_name

head(columbidae_response)
Alectroenas_madagascariensis            Aplopelia_larvata          Caloenas_nicobarica           Chalcophaps_indica           Claravis_godefrida          Claravis_mondetoura 
                  0.00000000                   0.00000000                   0.00000000                   0.03174603                   0.00000000                   0.00000000

Is the a phylogenetic signal for urban tolerance in the columbidae family

col_ut_phylo_signal <- phylosig(tree_pruned_to_columbidae, columbidae_response, method="lambda", test=TRUE)
col_ut_phylo_signal

Phylogenetic signal lambda : 0.164118 
logL(lambda) : -43.182 
LR(lambda=0) : 2.3677 
P-value (based on LR test) : 0.12387

Phylogenetic analysis containing all 160 species and produced a significant phylogenetic signal for urban tolerance (lambda: 0.16, LR(lambda=0): 2.37, p = 0.12)

Show the results for species

col_continuous_trait_evolution <- contMap(tree_pruned_to_columbidae, columbidae_response)


colourCount <- length(col_continuous_trait_evolution$cols)
col_continuous_trait_evolution$cols[1:colourCount] <- rev(col_continuous_trait_evolution$col[1:colourCount])

cte_all = plot(col_continuous_trait_evolution, outline=FALSE, fsize=0.3, lwd=1, leg.txt="Cities/Regional Pools", type = "fan")
